         <abstract>
            <p>The main problem when solving a Thue equation is the computation of the unit group of a certain number field. In this paper we show that the knowledge of a subgroup of finite index is actually sufficient. Two examples linked with the primitive divisor problem for Lucas and Lehmer sequences are given.</p>
          </abstract>
